---
const dashboardFeatures = [
  'How many months of expenses you have saved',
  'Whether your margin is growing or shrinking',
  'Your Emergency Fund vs. Storehouse breakdown',
];
---

<section class="py-24 md:py-40 bg-warm-stone grain-overlay">
  <div class="relative z-10 mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">

    <!-- Section header -->
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-storehouse-400 font-semibold text-sm tracking-widest uppercase reveal">
        The Joseph Principle
      </p>
      <h2 class="mt-4 font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl text-warm-white leading-[1.05] reveal reveal-delay-1">
        Ready for whatever<br />
        <em class="not-italic text-storehouse-400">comes next.</em>
      </h2>
    </div>

    <p class="mt-6 text-lg text-warm-white/70 leading-relaxed max-w-xl reveal reveal-delay-2">
      Life doesn't follow a budget. Medical bills arrive without warning. Cars break down at the worst time. Jobs disappear. And if your income varies &mdash; commission, freelance, seasonal &mdash; traditional budgets break immediately.
    </p>

    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-warm-white/70 leading-relaxed max-w-xl reveal reveal-delay-2">
      Storehouse uses what we call the <span class="font-semibold text-warm-white">Joseph Principle</span> &mdash; store during plenty so you're ready for lean.
    </p>

    <!-- Plenty / Lean grid -->
    <div class="mt-16 grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-4xl reveal reveal-delay-3">
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-warm-white/[0.07] backdrop-blur-sm border border-warm-white/10">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-storehouse-400">
          In plenty seasons
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-warm-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          When things are good, Storehouse helps you see it clearly and build your margin reserve &mdash; your cushion against whatever comes next.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="p-8 rounded-2xl bg-warm-white/[0.07] backdrop-blur-sm border border-warm-white/10">
        <h3 class="font-display text-2xl text-warm-white/90">
          In lean seasons
        </h3>
        <p class="mt-4 text-warm-white/70 leading-relaxed">
          When the unexpected hits &mdash; or income dips &mdash; you draw from your reserve without guilt or panic. That's what it's there for.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Dashboard features -->
    <div class="mt-16 max-w-2xl">
      <p class="text-warm-white/80 text-lg reveal reveal-delay-3">
        The dashboard shows your margin health:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 reveal reveal-delay-4">
        {dashboardFeatures.map((feature) => (
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3">
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5 text-storehouse-400 flex-shrink-0"
              fill="none"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              stroke-width="2"
              stroke="currentColor"
            >
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
            <span class="text-warm-white/80">{feature}</span>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Closing line -->
    <div class="mt-20 reveal reveal-delay-4">
      <p class="font-quote text-2xl sm:text-3xl text-warm-white/80 italic leading-snug max-w-2xl">
        "This isn't about predicting the future. It's about being ready for it."
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
